-- Bajaj Finserv, IDFC, Tata Motors and Hindustan Zinc: India Equity Preview
-- Unni Krishnan
-- 2010-06-29T02:44:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/bajaj-finserv-idfc-tata-motors-and-hindustan-zinc-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or  Sensex ,
gained 199.73, or 1.1 percent, to 17,774.26, its highest in a
week. The S&P CNX  Nifty  Index on the National Stock Exchange
rose 1.2 percent to 5,333.50. The BSE 200 Index increased 1.2
percent to 2,255.68. SGX CNX Nifty Index futures for July
delivery fell 0.2 to 5,330.0 at 10:40 a.m. in Singapore.  
 BGR Energy Systems Ltd.  (BGRL IN): The maker of equipment
for power, oil and petrochemical industries was rated “buy” in
new coverage by Goldman Sachs Group Inc. analysts led by  Ishan Sethi , who said the company will be a “key participant” in the
growth in power generation construction in India.  
 The analysts have a share-price estimate of 874 rupees for
BGR. The stock gained 1.2 percent to 708.50 rupees.  
 Hindustan Zinc Ltd  (HZ IN): India’s largest zinc producer
was raised to “buy” from “outperform” by  Pritam Lala , an
analyst at Batlivala & Karani Securities. The 12-month share-
price estimate is 1,316 rupees. The stock rose 2.1 percent to
982.85 rupees.  
 IndusInd Bank Ltd.  (IIB IN): The lender will raise 10
billion rupees ($216 million) by selling shares this financial
year, the Economic Times reported, citing two people familiar
with the matter. The money may be raised by selling shares to
institutions or by issue of global depository receipts,
according to the report. The stock increased 2 percent to 200.50
rupees.  
 Infrastructure Development Finance Co.  (IDFC IN): India’s
second-largest state-run lender for roads, ports and power
projects by value, plans to raise as much as $575 million
selling shares to institutional investors. The company will sell
stock for about 168.25 rupees apiece, according to a sale
document obtained by Bloomberg News. The stock climbed 1 percent
to 170.25 rupees.  
 Oil & Natural Gas Corp.  (ONGC IN) and  Indian Oil Corp. 
(IOCL IN): India may sell shares in Oil & Natural Gas and Indian
Oil after raising fuel prices last week, the Economic Times
reported, citing a government official it didn’t identify. The
government can raise money by selling its stake and the state-
run companies can issue additional shares to raise funds,
according to the newspaper. Indian Oil surged 5.2 percent to
397.60 rupees, while Oil & Natural Gas advanced 3.3 percent to
1,304.85 rupees.  
 Reliance Infrastructure Ltd.  (RELI IN): The electricity
distributor plans to spend 200 billion rupees on projects in
Mumbai, the company said in a statement yesterday, citing Chief
Executive Officer  Lalit Jalan . The stock rose 4.1 percent to
1,214.65 rupees.  
 GTL Infrastructure Ltd.  (GTLI IN): Saudi Telecom Co. may
buy a 10 percent to 15 percent stake in the venture created
after Reliance Infratel Ltd., a unit of Reliance Communications
Ltd., and GTL Infrastructure Ltd. merged this week, Business
Standard reported, citing people it didn’t identify.
GTL gained 3.9 percent to 47.10 rupees.  
 Steel Authority of India Ltd.  (SAIL IN): The nation’s
second-largest producer of the metal was raised to
“outperform” from “underperform” by Batlivala & Karani’s
Lala, with a share-price estimate of 229 rupees. The stock rose
1.9 percent to 198.9 rupees.  
 Tata Motors Ltd.  (TTMT IN): India’s largest commercial
vehicle maker and the owner of Jaguar and Land Rover plans to
raise as much as 47 billion rupees to expand operations and pare
debt accumulated for the purchase of the luxury brands, the
company said in a statement yesterday. Tata Motors rose 2.7
percent to 789.25 rupees.  
 Usha Martin Ltd.  (USM IN): The manufacturer of steel, wire
and cable products was raised to “buy” from “outperform” by
Batlivala & Karani’s Lala, with a share-price estimate of 121
rupees. The stock rose 1.1 percent at 85.7 rupees.  
